name: Load
description: WorldEvent.Load is fired when Minecraft loads a world. This event is fired when a world is loaded in WorldClient.WorldClient(NetHandlerPlayClient, WorldSettings, int, EnumDifficulty, Profiler) , MinecraftServer.loadAllWorlds(String, String, long, WorldType, String) , IntegratedServer.loadAllWorlds(String, String, long, WorldType, String) DimensionManager#initDimension(int) , and ForgeInternalHandler#onDimensionLoad(Load) . This event is not Cancelable . This event does not have a result. HasResult This event is fired on the MinecraftForge#EVENT_BUS .
